  "info" : {
    "title" : "BodyService",
    "description" : "BodyService exercises the three HttpRule.body modes (unset, \"*\", and a named\n field) across multiple HTTP verbs.  Each RPC asserts the canonical\n transcoder behaviour described in google/api/http.proto: with body unset\n every non-path field becomes a URL query parameter; with body=\"<field>\"\n that field is the request body and the rest become query parameters.",
